The *constr* suffix modifies the meaning of "fold", "iter", "map", ... iterators.
Instead of folding/iterating/mapping the elements of the collection itself,
we are folding/iterating/mapping only values of type Constr.t

(Beware that the choice of the actual postfix should probably be consistent
 with our choice of "Constr" vs. "Term" module names.)

================================================================================

INSTANCES

- fold_constr
  - Term.fold_constr
  - Context.Rel.Declaration.fold_constr
- iter_constr
  - Term.iter_constr
- map_constr
  - Term.map_constr
  - Term.map_constr_with_binders
